<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,374,725]" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,423,374,400]" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">Nomenclatural notes:—</emphasis>
<materialsCitation collectionCode="BR, U" collectorName="The &amp; Lambert's &amp; Martius's &amp; Examining &amp; Martius &amp; Berg &amp; Villavicencio &amp; Utrecht" country="Peru" county="Ruiz" location="The" municipality="Pozuzo" pageId="5" pageNumber="154" specimenCode="BR0000005418220" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="holotype">
<collectorName box="[423,467,374,400]" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">The</collectorName>
protologue mentions that the type of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ruiz ex Miquel" authorityYear="1847" box="[895,1125,375,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="Urostigma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="5" pageNumber="154" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="geminum">
<emphasis box="[895,1125,375,400]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">Urostigma geminum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was in 
<collectorName box="[1215,1329,374,400]" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">Lambert’s</collectorName>
herbarium and later in 
<collectorName box="[277,383,410,436]" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">Martius’s</collectorName>
herbarium. 
<collectorName box="[524,647,410,436]" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">Examining</collectorName>
the 
<collectionCode box="[700,737,411,437]" country="Brazil" name="Embrapa Agrobiology Diazothrophic Microbial Culture Collection" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">BR</collectionCode>
collection, the herbarium that acquired several 
<collectorName box="[1289,1376,410,436]" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">Martius</collectorName>
types, the 
<typeStatus box="[182,280,446,472]" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">holotype</typeStatus>
was found exactly as the protologue describes. 
<collectorName box="[850,904,447,473]" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">Berg</collectorName>
&amp; 
<collectorName box="[948,1097,446,472]" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">Villavicencio</collectorName>
(2004) and 
<collectorName box="[1246,1300,447,473]" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">Berg</collectorName>
(2007) were treating the duplicate of the 
<collectorName box="[460,544,482,508]" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">Utrecht</collectorName>
herbarium (
<collectionCode box="[685,707,482,508]" country="Netherlands" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15513" name="Nationaal Herbarium Nederland" pageId="5" pageNumber="154" type="Herbarium">U</collectionCode>
) as the 
<typeStatus box="[799,900,482,508]" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">holotype</typeStatus>
, but this must be corrected for the 
<collectionCode box="[1303,1340,483,509]" country="Brazil" name="Embrapa Agrobiology Diazothrophic Microbial Culture Collection" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">BR</collectionCode>
duplicate (
<specimenCode box="[144,370,518,545]" collectionCode="BR" country="Brazil" name="Embrapa Agrobiology Diazothrophic Microbial Culture Collection" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">BR0000005418220</specimenCode>
). 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:D92A87FDFFA4C66DFF3755FDFE88FD76:545C6030FFA4C66DFE3D5765FE3BFD82" box="[386,430,518,544]" country="Peru" county="Ruiz" municipality="Pozuzo" name="The" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">The</location>
protologue indicates that the type was collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[994,1048,519,545]" name="Peru" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">Peru</collectingCountry>
, with no exact location, but the label on the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:D92A87FDFFA4C66DFF3755FDFE88FD76:545C6030FFA4C66DFF6D5749FE8DFDE6" box="[210,280,554,580]" country="Peru" county="Ruiz" municipality="Pozuzo" name="Berlin" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">Berlin</location>
duplicate says that the collection was carried out in 
<collectingMunicipality box="[853,938,555,581]" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">Pozuzo</collectingMunicipality>
, which we are following. 
<bibRefCitation author="Miquel, F. A. W." box="[1222,1383,554,581]" pageId="5" pageNumber="154" pagination="78 - 106" refId="ref6631" refString="Miquel, F. A. W. (1853) Urticineae. In: Martius, C. F. P. (Ed.) Flora brasiliensis, vol. 4, par 1, Monachii, Lipsiae, Frid. Fleischer, pp. 78 - 106." type="book chapter" year="1853">Miquel (1853)</bibRefCitation>
noted that in the protologue it is mentioned that the epithet “gemina” comes from 
<collectingCounty box="[977,1033,590,616]" pageId="5" pageNumber="154">Ruiz</collectingCounty>
, so the authorship of the name should be described as “Ruiz ex Miquel” (Art. 46.5)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
